<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Tottenham chairman Daniel Levy was pictured arriving bright and early at Tottenham's Enfield training base on Friday as he looks to conclude Gareth Bale's return to the club. </p>

<p>As Sportsmail exclusively revealed on Wednesday, the formalities of a season-long loan deal worth £13million in wages has been finalised with an announcement expected imminently. </p>

<p>Bale is due to fly to London on Friday following some final medical checks in Madrid having already said goodbye to his team-mates at Real's Valdebebas training facility on Thursday.  </p>

<p>Levy was temperature tested by security staff on his arrival as part of ongoing protocol amid the coronavirus pandemic. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>
